objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate changes in overall skin appearance, as measured by dermatologist skin grading.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective
objectives.text: To assess changes in a range of skin health parameters.

endpoints.name: Improvement in Skin Appearance
endpoints.text: Improvements in skin health parameters will be evaluated by dermatologist grading at Baseline and Week 12.

endpoints.name: Improvement in Skin Health Parameters
endpoints.text: Improvement in skin plumpness, fine lines and wrinkles, pigmentation, tone and texture, redness, firmness, elasticity, radiance, and appearance of crepey skin. Participant perceptions of skin health will be evaluated through subject-specific questionnaires at Baseline, Week 2, Week 4, Week 6, Week 8, Week 10, and Week 12.
